headline: These Energy Dividend Stocks Print Money
summary: Williams receives roughly 91% of its earnings from predictable contracts.  Cash flows across the energy sector tend to be more variable due to commodity price volatility.  Energy Transfer (NYSE: ET), Kinder Morgan (NYSE: KMI), and Williams (NYSE: WMB) operate money-printing energy midstream assets.

headline: Kinder Morgan Maintains Strong Dividend Appeal with Growing Project Backlog
summary: Kinder Morgan, Inc. (NYSE:KMI) is one of the 10 best dividend stocks according to Jim Cramer. UBS has reiterated a Buy rating on the company’s stock, with a price target of $38. One of the largest energy infrastructures in North America, Kinder Morgan, Inc. (NYSE:KMI) owns and operates 83,000 miles of pipelines and 141 terminals. […]
